Abdomen. Brown. Terminalia (
Fig. 22–24
): tergite 9 tapering gradually distally to broad, quadrate apex, with slender apicolateral process; sternite 9 spiculate except on basal portion, posterior margin with narrow, moderately convex median extension bearing two long setae. Gonocoxite straight, moderately stout, 2.4 x longer than basal width; gonostylus nearly straight, 0.60 length of gonocoxite, proximal ½ moderately pilose. Parameres (
Fig. 23
